reviews.text: To be able to slowly saunter around, leisurely allowing brilliant works of art, some thousands of years old, to permeate your soul, that is what the Kimbell freely offers the visitors and residents of Fort Worth. Even the very building is a work of art, walk slowly by the reflecting pool and search for the hidden rock garden. I've been in love with the Kimbell for 30 years, since as a child I first looked, wide-eyed at the works of Monet, a special exhibit they were holding. Thus began my love for art. I encourage you to visit the free exhibit at very least, and find out when an exhibition that interests you is coming and go to that. But just go.

One of the things I love from Fort Worth is that most of the attractions are free. This is without exception one if the nicest free attractions. The paintings of the realism era are gorgeous. Feels like if they were pictures of how good they are painted. The prehispánic collection and Asian collection are worth seeing. Take some beautiful pictures in their gardens and fountain outside the museum.
Great place to visit for people of all ages. Large array of art. Very nice. I would recommend this museum to singles, couples and families. You will have a great time. I did

The artwork and building are great. I only wished that they charged something in order to keep the riffraff out. This is one of the few remaining places of high culture, but too many of the visitors don't seem to really respect it. They seem to go there just because its free.

The Kimbell Art Museum always has interesting exhibits, and there is more than enough art to explore in the museum. Visits typically take a few hours, and there is a gift shop and a café if you'd like to take a break from browsing the galleries. The parking can be a little awkward as you'll most likely have to parallel park off the side of a two-way, two-lane street. Overall a fun place to visit every so often - better for adults, teens, and older kids as I don't believe they have a ton of options for keeping young children entertained.

The collection is well worth a visit. We love the extensive Remington and Russell collections. Also Stuart Davis and other American art. The collection keeps expanding. The view out the front of the lobby is lovely. The museum is free.

This is a beautiful museum.  The only downside to this review is that I made a special trip here from Austin only to find out that most of the 2nd floor is closed for renovation.  I wish this had been posted on their website.  They have also stopped selling their full-size art posters.

This is where you go for Remington's and Russell's. They have paintings, sculptures and cool letters that Russell wrote to friends with illustations.  Pretty cool.  A couple of other cool non-western things there and definitely worth going.  You can walk to the Kimbell from there and there IS free parking on the north side of the Amon Carter building. Only problem is, there is lots of construction going on. In fact, it's pretty bad. But, it's manueverable with a little effort.  Worth the trip and there's lots of great  places to eat and drink in Ft. Worth now.

The front desk lady was friendly and informative. The rest of the staff was non-intrusive which was welcomed. The museum was clean and the exhibits were interesting. The most memorable experience was seeing the rainbows coming from the ceiling. The best part was that admission was free.

I visited a few years back and recall the impression I had of looking at some of these paintings; the size and enormity of some of them really needs to be appreciated up close. Though many of these were painted during the early stages of photography, the paintings seem to be one of the best ways for the scenery to come alive. Even when paintings worked well as a median, some of the best photography of native Americans had also been on display.
Wonderful place to learn about the Black, Hispanic & Indian in the Old West and today
There's a lot of my relatives in the history book in this museum!
This place was an Interesting museum but the building is now up for sale.

This was an excellent museum experience. My friend and I decided to pop into this museum on a whim the day before I left town and man am I glad we did! The staff were quite knowledgeable and answered lots of random questions I had.
Western heritage is not multicultural

This was a good stop on our trip through Texas.  Was not crowded (due to rodeo and stock show downtown Fort Worth).  Museum was great and everyone working there was very friendly.  This is definitely a tourist trap, but worth the stop if you have time.  Only reason not 5 stars alot of construction in the area had many attractions closed.

Fun place to visit for the entire family. So much history about the cattle selling days of old and the meat packing originated here back in the early 1900’s! The museum is tiny but packs a punch with memorabilia! See pictures and stories of the real cow girls too! Learn about the key roles Swift and Armour played in shaping the meat packing business too. Also some American Indian influences around the same time in the stockyards area.
Interesting to read all the history behind the stockyards. Lots of old items to browse through. Small museum but rich in history.
Good place to learn about Fort Worth. Fun to watch the long horn cattle being led down the street.

Unexpected jewel in the Fort Worth historic Stockyards area.  Located in the historic Livestock Exchange Building, it has numerous interesting artifacts - do the scavenger hunt!  Also has a small gift shop with Fort Worth and Texana gifts - including jellies and salsas.  Operated by volunteers, the sales and the small entrance fee of $2.00 support the efforts of the North Fort Worth Historic Society whose mission includes keeping the history of the stockyards alive.

This is the Texas I wanted to find. I'm in Dallas on vacation, and while it's an amazing city (Go to Pecan Lodge!), the stockyards was the experience I was secretly hoping for. I loved every minute of it. You simply must go if you're in the area. 
Buy a cowboy hat (they're GREAT at keeping the sun off your neck! WHO KNEW?!), ride a longhorn and have your picture taken, watch the cattle drive down main street and have a beer in an authentic old-west saloon. 
This is a memory I'll always treasure =)

We ate at "Risky's." Had the 7oz. Flat Iron Steak; Medium Rare w/ Steak fries. Best Flat Iron Steak I've Ever Had! Pricing was good and not too expensive. Pretty Good Service; Our Server "Monica?" I think recommended the Flat Iron Steak: Excellent! The 6oz. Tenderloin is Superb as well! (What i had the last time we went there. (8 years ago)? Truly, Consistent. Worth "the wait!!"

We have our son and his family visiting from out of town and so we decided to go to the rodeo at the Fort Worth stockyards had a very enjoyable time and the kids enjoyed it as well. Definitely a family friendly atmosphere and good food and places to see as well as shopping. Overall we had a really great time.

A must-see for those visiting the Dallas/Fort Worth area!  The Stockyards are honestly a fun time. There's plenty of shopping for souvenirs of all kinds, from cowboy boots and hats to treats and Risky's BBQ for some great food. There is also a maze you can run through for a small price that's great fun as well as street shows and a cattle drive that runs twice daily!
As well as photo opportunities and other fun things to do.
Just be mindful there is a price to park which is under 20$ and is for all day.

Ft.Worth classic place to visit. If you go, make sure you are there for a cattle drive (11am and 4pm) or it won't be worth it.  The cattle drive is pretty short though - maybe 5 minutes of watching them go by  this is not what I would consider a frugal stop - $7 to park, $3 per person for petting zoo, charges for maze activity and "viewing area", and then of course shopping and food if you do that (we brought snacks and drinks from home). We did the petting zoo which was nice, but the animals are behind a short fence. You can pet and feed them, but can't hold them or walk around with them.

Great place to take the family. The main walkway is free to enjoy. You have to pay to get to see the Japanese garden, which I did not do (this time). There's plenty of garden to see that you can easily spend (or waste) a couple hours here. Tons of beauty that is well maintained by the staff. Oh, and the front desk staff is helpful and kind.

Well,  I was just there for orientation very briefly, I'm at West Jeanette supervisor of maintenance. My brief experience with her; great attitude seems to be really spunky in the morning.. her crew seems to really relate to her she interacts well with them.. like I said my experience was brief but I'm going back, the initial lives that I've got was that they enjoy working with her. Can't wait to go back

Wonderful place. You could spend all day here.  There is no entrance fee for it except Japanese garden.
Lot of trees and its naturally amazing views. 
Pool area is awesome with color fishes. Ducks are beautiful.

This is a truly beautiful and peaceful garden. It's ideal for picnics, leisure walks, exploring and learning. It's Free and there is a variety of pleasant sitting areas to quietly read a book while you embrace the fragrance from the exquisite blooms. Perhaps a family day including a picnic and exploring the different forest species that will truly amaze you. 
If you are ready to enjoy the beauty of a delightful exotic yet serene experience feel free to visit the reception desk for your admission ticket to the Japanese tea garden. There you will enjoy relaxing sounds of streams and smell the beautiful spring flowers in bloom. I will always recommended this Fort Worth attraction to visitors and frequently visit myself. 
Thanks for providing such a happy place.

Loved the variety of flowers and landscaped sections.  Everything was beautiful and vibrant, and the fragrant scents of the blends of flowers were intoxicating.  I had such a pleasant time walking the grounds, seeing families and friends, even kids, enjoying themselves!  And all the staff were great as well!

Excellent staff and fantastic barbeque. The meat was cooked to perfection and the sauce was lovely. The coleslaw was slightly sweet but combined with the rest of the meal I'm not sure I would rather have it any other way. The atmosphere was well crafted and the other guests were friendly. It was an excellent experience.

Great service now! Hamburger is excellent! BBQ is very good.  Steaks are a mixed bag.  May be the only place in the area that understands that hand- cut fries have to be blanch fried,  cooked,  then fried to order so they aren't leathery with a raw potato taste. They understand French fries!

The sliced  brisket was great - very tender, but I didn't like the Turkey. It was pretty slimy, and I prefer it a more natural meaty texture. Also, parking can be an issue because the place is so popular for the end of week crowd.
Always great BBQ! Been going to Railhead for years always same great taste. And cold frosty beers! Nice to enjoy the nice weather out on the patio.

Love the place before 4 pm. Don't go after then the barteneder is rude and not a people person. She makes the trip not very fun. We went for 3 days straight and for 2 days she was completely ugly and told us not to come back. The other bartenders are amazing.  We weren't the only ones to have a problem. Another couple even complained to the manager on her.  If you go and there is a heavier set girl with glasses and ponytail you might as well leave because she is rude and is even rude to elderly people. It was so bad she even flipped me off when I left because we didn't give her a good tip.
Old fashioned hamburger joint. They have old tables, old grocery displays and tons of memorabilia on the walls. Great Hamburgers! Great quality! A must go to if you are in Ft. Worth.

Despite being super busy they got our orders to us pretty quickly and everything was correct. However the bathroom was having issues flushing properly and the tank to the toilet was cracked. Food was good otherwise but might wait out a bathroom visit.

The Chili Cheeseburger was so delicious it was Magical... I couldn't have asked for a better burger on my Birthday! The sweet lady who took our order at the counter was so kind and friendly.  This experience is one filled w nothing but highlights!
Great hamburgers and has been here since 1946. They also have great onion rings and they have a homemade ranch dipping sauce which is very tasty.
Delicious cheeseburger and fries with friendly staff. This is a Ft Worth tradition! I love the quaint atmosphere and how friendly everyone is here. Even the other customers are very friendly.
A+++++. Great place for date night! Love the intimacy of such a small place.  Don't forget to bring a bottle of wine (they have glasses and bottle opener). Definitely get dessert! Oh, and cash only!

This tiny little restaurant is fantastic! The service was prompt, the atmosphere inside was cozy, and the food was outrageously good! I had the veal with rissoto cake, which was wonderfully savory. Even my date who hates rissoto had to admit that this was excellent. My date ended up with the tenderloin, which he said was some of the best he's ever had.

Just keep in mind, the restaurant is very small and fills up fast inside, though they also have outdoor seating. The chairs inside are not the comfiest, but the food definitely outweighed that in my estimation. 

I haven't had Italian food this tasty at a restaurant since I was last in Italy. It's a quirky little place with great food, so I highly recommend it.

The food here is amazing. I started with the soup of the day, which was pumpkin, and could've stopped there and been happy. It was very thick and creamy. Then I had the Cornish hen with lemon cream pasta which was delicious. For dessert I had the panna cotta with strawberries. I'd be there every week if they weren't so expensive. Also they only take cash so you have to plan ahead.

The best Italian restaurant in North Texas. Chef driven with fresh ingredients and a cozy atmosphere. Easily the best red bell pepper soup I've ever had. Maybe the best soup I've had. It's amazing. Don't skip the house made pasta and the apple and pear cake.  Best of all, it's BYOB. Bring a nice bottle, the food deserves it.

Best Italian food in Fort Worth by far!  The food is made with care and you can taste the love put in it.  Not just my favorite Italian place in Fort Worth, but my favorite restaurant.  Get there early because the place packs up, definitely worth the wait if you don't though.  AMAZING food!

I hate to do it... I really enjoyed this place and the atmosphere but today was the last straw... I wanna wanted to call in an order and had to wait 7 minuets before I hung up and come in to place it. I stood at the front do another 10 minuets and no on came!!! So I sat in the car and started this review, convincingly enough 7 woman pull up of different characteristics (and I NEVER use race as an issue but being someone who works in restaurants I observed) and followed back in behind them. They get seated IMMEDIATELY and I’m back at front for another couple of minutes before Juan was nice enough to greet me and take my order.... my advice.... don’t have your window where people walking in can see all of your staff laughing at the window! I’ve worked in restaurants for at least 5 years and can only tolerate so much. Juan definitely deserves a raise if he’s not a manager because I see him taking on all the responsibilities of EVERY position.

The food was absolutely amazing, our waiter was extremely friendly and very attentive. We got service less than a minute of us being seated. It's not the chefs first rodeo either, he seemed very experienced in the art of culinary foods. Overall one of the best restaurants I've ever visited.

In town for the first time ever a dance competition and wanted to try something unique. Service was fast and helpful, and gracious when we took forever to order.  Our party of five got all different items. Drinks, appetizers, and entrees and desserts. Food was great although we never were offered the bread I read about in reviews. Plus, despite showing up before 3 on a Sunday, the lunch portions offered in the menu aren’t available. Lastly I appreciate all the local beers on the drink menu, but you no longer had three of them and fail to post the prices of the ones you did have. I’m not going to freak, but I should have been forewarned of an 11 dollar bottle of local beer....Especially since we had two! lol. That being said, it was a nice visit. We will come back next year.

Great spot wouldn't have known about it if my roommate didn't point it out though.
It is a restaurant in a renovated gas station which sounds weird but was actually pretty cool. The food was amazing but the drinks were somewhat lacking. I have been a few times brought some friends and they've been consistent.

This was a great find. Great service, great food and the bread pudding was to die for. My only little complaint would be the chicken being a little more cooked. Ashley was a great server and I really recommend this restaurant.

The food was delicious. We went on Spring Break and the service was great. There is also a bar and hotel attached with some interesting history to read about! If your just looking for a drink or a good meal this is the place for you. Kid Friendly.

Pure disgusting. We're NOT picky eaters so I am crazy mad at this place. We ordered a cheese burger all the way with mustard, received a plain burger with nothing on it. Nothing. Then they acted like we ordered it that way. Come on, that's nuts. I ordered a side salad that came with expired dressing. The bread was ROCK hard. We couldn't physically chew it. We had to spit it out. Ridiculous. My meal had zero flavor, was over cooked, and the waitress didn't care the food was terrible. She barely checked on us and we had to stop three other waitresses just to fill up our drinks. The only good thing were the fries.

Food is great atmosphere is fun (bar stools are hourse saddles). Had a choice between H3 and Cattleman's. Walked into both and this place was much more inviting. Clean, fun good food and service. Had the Tomahawk Pork chop, awesome would order again every one else had steaks and I heard no complaints.

This place was great. The smoky flavor the wood fire imparts to the steak makes it so much better than your typical steak. Their medium was more red than your typical East coast medium, and the steak was MUCH better and more tender as a result.  H3 knows what they are doing!  Great atmosphere too with mounted bison, longhorns, and a mountain lion.
It was a great all around experience for a late night dinner!  The atmosphere was good and the waiter we had was great and attentive!  Highly recommend this place for anyone visiting the Stock Yards!

I heard such great things about this place.   A couple of my friends and I got together on a Friday night to eat here.  We had the weirdest waiter, I experienced an unfriendly environment at this place.  
We ordered drinks which took forever to arrive there was only three other families in the restaurant they weren’t busy at all.  And then we headed out the waiter hadn’t even brought the ticket yet.  We had asked him for the tab twice.  So we just left cash on the table for the drinks and left. 

I really wanted to try the food here

I wish I could give it 0 stars! A one star is an under statement! This place is under new management and is absolutely horrible!!!! Got to meet the new owner today because they charged me two children’s plate  when I only ordered one. He began to state that I ordered two and that was what I needed to pay. As I explained that I only have one child and have no reason to order two. He rudely snatched the ticket out of my hand and walked off. He then sent someone else to bring my ticket back. His customer service is soo disgusting and I cannot express how upsetting it is to see someone with a leadership position not only act this way towards their customers but also be this example to the fellow employees. I was a loyal customer prior to the change of management and change of food quality. This was a place I recommended to all my friends and family. I will NOT EVER go back to this restaurant. Please don’t waste your time going here. I can assure you it will only leave you disappointed!

If I could have given no stars, I would have. I will NOT eat at this restaurant ever again. First of all, my food arrived well after the rest of my party. In fact, I had to ask twice to get it to arrive. Then, I was only given the tacos - no sides. It took until we got our checks for the sides to even arrive. The biggest complaint I have is that they charged my credit card wrong. I have a photo image of the receipt that clearly shows the total as well as an incorrect total balance charged to my card (not pending - charged). I will be disputing this charge and never returning. How unethical can you be to blatantly mis-charge a card? WORST PLACE EVER.

First time trying out was a Sunday around 5. We were basically the only ones there. When we first walked in it took them a bit to acknowledge us and figure out which table they wanted us to sit at. The queso is not worth the price but the dinners were decent. The tamales are good but the chimis are more than half full with rice. A kids soda is $2.50 which is kinda high IMO. Their twist on a white Russian is pretty tasty tho, has a little bit of a bite. The decor is pretty cool. All in all it wasn't a terrible experience but I don't think we will be back.

Had a large family party of 25+ish including a few kids (reserved ahead of time). One server on our entire table was craziness that took a hour to get all the drinks, the bday guy ordered first and was literally the last to get his plate 2+hrs later poor server was overwhelmed..but the salsa is delicious though and the alcohol was tasty 👍. Id go again but not in a large party..
Nice late lunch with friends. Good service and food. No waiting to be seated. Love the quail eggs!
It's so fresh! Neat place downtown. Kind of a hole in the wall, but so worth it. Price is fair for what you get. I had sushi, my mom had a bento box. Both were amazing!

This place was amazing as always. The waitor was on point the whole time. Drinks never went dry and food came out fresh and fast. If you like sushi and never tried this place it is definitely worth the stop.

TL;DR: Come back when they get good chefs back in the kitchen.
In the past this has been great, but yesterday (2018/12/27) while the service was good, the sushi was terrible. There was over an hour wait, the rice was dry, the sake was warm at best, and almost all the sushi was dry and lacking flavor. We weren't the only ones to think so. A group next to us was given free sake and still got up and left in disgust. Walking back to the bathroom passes the kitchen and it looked disordered too, if not dirty.

When we called to see if the place was open because it was new years day we were greeted with "what do you need" having been here a few years ago and really enjoyed it we decided to go anyways despite the rude call. when we entered there were two tables seated in the whole restaurant and were sat by an extremely rude hostess and then proceeded to wait 15 minutes before any server decided to come talk to us, mind you that there is literally two other parties of four in the entire restaurant with different waiters serving them and still weren't greeted for 15 minutes, long enough that we picked out our entire meal and drinks two cocktails and three rolls while another table seated after us were greeted and served before we even saw our waitress. The cocktails were the only good part of the experience. We then proceeded to wait 30 minutes for three rolls to be made and the table next to us that was seated after had two rolls and oysters already brought out to them and had almost finished eating by the time our 3 rolls had arrived which we finished before the waitress even asked how the meal was. After the unbearable wait watching other tables arrive around us and be fed before us, the service was absolutely inexcusable for two people in a nearly empty restaurant.
Really great food. A bit overpriced but the portions are large. One of our guests at our table didn't get food because the waitress made a mistake. It was easily resolved. No problem. Food is good.

The food was great, as usual. You can't go wrong ordering something from the grilled menu. (But their enchiladas and such are good , too!). I had the Guadalajara, which is beef fajitas with bacon wrapped shrimp stuffed with cheese and peppers. Fantastic. The portion size was big enough that that I had enough to take home for another meal. 

Our server was super friendly and got us everything we needed in a timely manner. There was a shift change during our visit, and it went smoothly, with our next server being as good as the first.

There can be a long wait time during peak hours, so I would suggest going other times. But, definitely go!

The food was amazing. I could Seriously move to Texas just for this restaurant! The staff was very friendly and really fast. We never had to ask for anything. The waiter we had was great! He recommended us food and drinks and they were amazing! I would definitely recommend this place but try to make a reservation or expect a 45 minute wait time for a table unless you want to eat on the patio. Perfect place!

Amazing Mexican food served with Mariachi serenading you at the top of their Lungs while you eat!  Out side dinning  is avaliable.  Lovely setting inside as well as out.  Nice for family, for large groups, Parties, Businesses,  Romantic setting, can be seen by drinking by. Prices are reasonable, Mixed Drinks, Beer & Wine, they also have Dessert.  ENJOY💋🍀

Always great food. The salsa is amazing. Haven't been in years because we just don't get to Fort Worth like we used to but beyond deleting some of my old favorites to keep up with what's trending, it was every bit as good as remembered.

I have always loved this place. The food , service and atmosphere are great. I went here recently for an office Christmas Party though, and the service was not up its usual caliber although the food was excellent. Long story short, they comped our meal and gave everyone a free desert. I was shocked they did this. First class place, I'll be back.

Excellent food and service. A great place to celebrate a special occasion. Prices are high, but commensurate to the quality. You will not be disappointed and if you are a manager will be sure to accommodate accordingly. 99% of the time it has been excellent. The weak spot seems to be service from waitstaff tapers off toward the end of the meal however they're also not pushy about getting you out the door to turn the table over.

Had dinner with a large group of friends and the service was excellent. The entire meal was incredible. The courses were timed to allow for enjoying the meal while enjoying the conversation with friends.

Went for anniversary celebration.  Be sure to mention a special occasion to the hostess as you will get a VIP dessert, not complementary but discounted.  Wife had a martini to start.  I stuck with water. We started with tuna tartare and crab cake for appetizers.  Delicious.  She had Sea Bass as her entree and I did the dry aged rib eye, a tad large for me at 16oz.  Both delicious too.  Had sides of onion rings (gigantic serving) and potato au gratin.  Left the place stuffed and wallet took a beating....+$250.  Luckily we don’t do this too often 😀

Amazing place. We went for thanksgiving and I must saw the service, staff and food is exceptional. And the restaurant itself is a gorgeous. I've been to a million restaurants and this one is one of my top 3 as far as fine dining experiences go. I'd recommend to anyone for any special occasion or if you just want to treat yourself and indulge in a little decadence.

This is a great place to have a business dinner for a good Texas feel. The food is pretty great most of the time. Nothing says “Texas Steakhouse” like this place. They even have a rooftop dining area if you want a good look at downtown while having dinner and an adult beverage. This is a good spot for a romantic date night. Cowboy hats are welcome.

Nice restaurant and I suggest you valet vs the park and walk. The walk isn’t bad, but the parking fee is steep. I had the chicken fried steak with mashed potatoes and it was delicious. The appetizers were tasteful, too. Definitely reserve your time before going or call to assure there’s room if you’re already nearby.

From the greeting to the table service, the excellent attention from May, our server, and the dishes, themselves. Perfection. A bit edgy sometimes, with a 'play' on traditional tortilla soup that was very tasty and satisfying to a interpretation of the tamale, my guest and I both felt the overall meal was spot-on. We will return. Note that, as a chef, I read all reviews of a new (to me) establishment, Always the low rating, where I can usually discern valid complaints from ignorant complaints. Anyone can write a positive review of a restaurant, but what are its short-comings. Reata has wonderful atmosphere, superb service and delicious and somewhat edgy offerings on the menu. Highly recommended for a higher-end dining experience.

Beautiful restaurant near Sundance Square with excellent reputation in the community. Prices are not bad for the ambiance but we were a little disappointed in the food. Regardless, we would go back in the future should we visit Fort Worth. We had chicken fried steak and it was good but I have had much better in this area, Next time I would order some other dish. Again, I would definitely return notwithstanding as the ambiance is very nice.

Awesome food and service! Everything we've eaten here is amazing! The wine was also excellent. The atmosphere is relaxing and authentic rustic country at the same time. A little on the pricey side, but not unreasonable. Reservations recommended.

We had a group Valentine’s dinner here the day after Valentine’s and thoroughly enjoyed our experience. The restaurant in in a quaint little old house that has been renovated in a French inspired restaurant. The wait staff was friendly and the chefs prepared a wonderful meal for us. Pricing was very reasonable and a great wine selection as well. I would recommend the beef tenderloin with peppercorn sauce!

It was weird to be at a French restaurant and have a young waitress call us love, darling, etc. She was American so it seemed very pretentious. The food was delicious. The gnocchi were light and very tasty. Everything we had was delicious except the dessert. The crepes were overwhelmed by the flavor in the cherry and the grand marnier. Oddly, the nutella and banana one was the best and didn't overwhelm the crepe. The atmosphere was pleasant - very personable - unlike a lot of the other high-end restaurants in Fort Worth. The service was excellent - and she knew not to reach over a diner.

I have little to compare the reboot of St. Emilion to, not having eaten there before the changes that I'm reading about in the other reviews. All I can say is that when my wife and I went last week to celebrate our anniversary, our reception was cordial and even accommodating. She had received a gift certificate, which had expired at the end of October, but the restaurant still honored it. The food was superb; and Rusty, who was waiting on us that night, doubling his role as a chef, was extremely helpful and informative about menu choices. Best of all, we left with change in our pockets. Something I was not expecting at all!
Excellent food, nice quiet family atmosphere. Great service. Reasonably priced wine choices

The most romantic restaurant in Fort Worth, Saint-Emilion is our favorite for anniversaries and special occasions. It is a delightfully authentic French dining experience. The dining room is tiny and the service impeccably personal. You won't find better French food on this continent. Also, check out their Bistro menu for a delicious modestly priced prixe fixe dinner at the early seating on Tuesdays and Wednesdays.

This has become one of my favorite spots after just two visits. I went for dinner the first time and fell in love with the grit tots and biscuits with honey butter. Amazing start to my meal and the shrimp and grits entree was also incredible. My fiancé had steak which was also very well prepared and juicy. Second time we had brunch and it was amazing! The chicken and waffles were a generous portion with a delicious hot sauce. The French toast had great texture and flavor. I would highly recommend the biscuits and grit tots, must try if you dine here.

This place is assume and the food is great. A nice spin on the hot sauce. I had the shrimp and grits nice size shrimps and grits soft and the seasoning great. I'm from Charleston SC, so I know what good food taste like. 
I could go on and on but you gotta go there and see for yourself.

Have had brunch here twice, both times were excellent. After a night of partying, its hard to beat chicken n waffles with a mimosa. The biscuits are always warm out of the oven, and the gravy was pretty good. The chicken & waffles is a great deal for under $20, its a ton of food that will set you on a path to Deep Couch City. I am salivating just thinking about it.

All of the food was fresh, creative, flavorful and delicious.  The cocktails we're excellent as well.  It has a rustic farmhouse vibe which compliments the southern themed menu.  The atmosphere was lively and energetic and the bar has a unique design with a decent amount of seating.

Go for a good brunch experience. Great food and soothing ambience. 
Must try— Short rib hash and biscuits.
